			<description><![CDATA[<p>Atari, a global publisher and developer of interactive games is seeking Senior Mobile Producer. The Senior Mobile Producer will responsible for evaluating, developing and managing mobile game development projects concurrently from inception to market release. This position will be responsible to ensure that project goals are met including: testing, quality, timeliness, and budget. This position will work with external developers/studios worldwide to make certain all contractual requirements are met in each milestone delivered, as well as validate and authorize milestone payments to third parties and contractors.</p><p>Responsibilities</p><p>&bull;&nbsp; Work closely with external development studios to set, assign, manage and complete design, production, QA, and testing tasks.<br />&bull;&nbsp; Communicate creative feedback, bugs, and schedule expectations to external development studios.<br />&bull;&nbsp; Create specifications and documents that communicate project vision, short and long term goals, budget, and schedule to development teams, and regularly communicate project status to management.<br />&bull;&nbsp; Manage multiple projects simultaneously to ensure projects are being developed on time, on budget, and at an acceptable level of quality.<br />&bull;&nbsp; Coordinate all efforts with brand management, marketing, sales, and operations.<br />&bull;&nbsp; Ensure that all projects are achieving quality and fun goals while actively managing the schedule and development milestone deliverables.<br />&bull;&nbsp; Manage day-to-day development issues; identify problems in advance and drive creative solutions.<br />&bull;&nbsp; Facilitate communication across the project team; clearly communicate tasks and responsibilities to staff.</p><p>Skills<br />&bull;&nbsp; Team Leadership<br />&bull;&nbsp; Clearly Communicating vision and goals<br />&bull;&nbsp; Gaining team consensus, conflict resolution<br />&bull;&nbsp; Game design input<br />&bull;&nbsp; Project Management</p><p>Qualifications</p><p>&bull;&nbsp; Strong communication and writing skills, with experience communicating both creative and technical feedback.<br />&bull;&nbsp; Shipped at least 3 notable mobile titles as Lead Producer from start to finish.<br />&bull;&nbsp; Experience driving creative vision and managing design on shipped mobile titles.<br />&bull;&nbsp; Minimum 5 years industry experience.<br />&bull;&nbsp; Broad knowledge of games and the games industry.<br />&bull;&nbsp; A passion for playing games from multiple genres.<br />&bull;&nbsp; Knowledge of the submission process for mobile platform.<br />&bull;&nbsp; Have knowledge of the competitive and industry landscape<br />&bull;&nbsp; Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree</p><p>About Atari</p><p>Atari (www.atari.com) is a multi-platform, global interactive entertainment and licensing company. The original innovator of video gaming, founded in 1972, Atari owns and/or manages a portfolio of more than 200 games and franchises, including world renowned brands like Asteroids&reg;, Centipede&reg;, Missile Command&reg;, Pong&reg;, Test Drive&reg;, Backyard Sports&reg;, Deer Hunter&reg;, Ghostbusters&reg;, and Rollercoaster Tycoon&reg;. Atari capitalizes on these powerful properties by delivering compelling games online (i.e. browser, Facebook&reg; and digital download), on smartphones and tablets and other connected devices. The Company also develops and distributes interactive entertainment for video game consoles from Microsoft, Nintendo and Sony. As a licensor, Atari extends its brand and franchises into other media, merchandising and publishing categories.</p><p>For more information about Atari games and the latest news:</p><p>- Visit our website: www.atari.com<br />- Like us on Facebook: www.facebook.com/atari<br />- Follow us on Twitter: www.twitter.com/atari<br />- Subscribe to our YouTube Channel: www.youtube.com/atari</p><p>Atari has offices in Los Angeles, New York, Paris, Lyon and London.</p><p>Atari is an Equal Opportunity Employer.</p>]]></description>
