			<description><![CDATA[<p>
Senior Data Analyst<br />
<br />
Atari seeks a highly motivated and seasoned analyst for their mobile games team!&nbsp; The successful candidate should have a proven track record of analytics, preferably from a games or internet/e-commerce company, with excellent SQL-writing ability. In addition, the candidate should enjoy combining analytic skills with business acumen to provide product teams and senior management with data, insights and knowledge that will drive continued success.&nbsp;<br />
The Senior Data Analyst will report to the Senior Director, Analytics and will work closely with product and production teams as well as key decision-makers on a daily basis supporting tactical and strategic decisions with insight and recommendations based on exploratory, data driven analytics. The candidate should enjoy both working with people and performing detailed technical analyses.<br />
&nbsp;<br />
Responsibilities:<br />
&bull; Provide operational reporting information to product managers and leadership teams on game performance<br />
&bull; Perform detailed data exploration and validation to understand the differences between data noise and data points<br />
&bull; Develop new insights and analyses that inform executive decision makers strengthening game success and enhancing user experience<br />
Required Skillset:<br />
<br />
&bull; Several years&rsquo; experience performing quantitative analysis, preferably for a game, internet or e-commerce company<br />
&bull; Excellent SQL skills coupled with an understanding of Big Data analytics and platforms; data modeling experience a plus<br />
&bull; High proficiency with Excel as well as experience with data presentation or visualization tools and techniques<br />
&bull; Ability to execute research projects, and generate practical results and recommendations<br />
&bull; Proven ability of delivery work in multiple projects in a fast-paced environment with changing deadlines and requirements<br />
&bull; Excellent organizational, communication and interpersonal skills with experience of communicating complex analysis with a business perspective to leadership teams<br />
&bull; Enjoy working in an individual capacity as well as in teams<br />
&bull; B.S. or B.A. required in in math, economics, engineering or some other related field<br />
&bull; A good understanding of basic statistics, A/B testing and use of tools like R, SAS or similar an added bonus<br />
&bull; Experience with Linux or Unix based platforms, shell scripting, scripting languages such as PERL or PHP an added plus</p>
<p>
About Atari<br />
Atari (www.atari.com) is a multi-platform, global interactive entertainment and licensing company. The original innovator of video gaming, founded in 1972, Atari owns and/or manages a portfolio of more than 200 games and franchises, including world renowned brands like Asteroids&reg;, Centipede&reg;, Missile Command&reg;, Pong&reg;, Test Drive&reg;, Backyard Sports&reg;, Deer Hunter&reg;, Ghostbusters&reg;, and Rollercoaster Tycoon&reg;. Atari capitalizes on these powerful properties by delivering compelling games online (i.e. browser, Facebook&reg; and digital download), on smartphones and tablets and other connected devices. The Company also develops and distributes interactive entertainment for video game consoles from Microsoft, Nintendo and Sony. As a licensor, Atari extends its brand and franchises into other media, merchandising and publishing categories.<br />
For more information about Atari games and the latest news:<br />
- Visit our website: www.atari.com<br />
- Like us on Facebook: www.facebook.com/atari<br />
- Follow us on Twitter: www.twitter.com/atari<br />
- Subscribe to our YouTube Channel: www.youtube.com/atari<br />
Atari has offices in Los Angeles, New York, Paris, Lyon and London.<br />
Atari is an Equal Opportunity Employer.</p>
